			<p><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">
			&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;We should always recognize the champions of Norrath that we've encountered.  These people go out of their way to help others, or are one's who have done extraordinary deeds to benefit Norrathian life.  If you've met someone you feel belongs on this list, e-mail me with your story (<a href="mailto:ludarian@hotmail.com">Ludarian@hotmail.com</a>)<br><br>
 			&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<font color="#FAE42B"><b>Elles</b></font> - It's my honor to submit Elles as our first entry on our Gold List.  Though this list wasn't intended for guild members, I feel it's more than appropriate to add Elles to our Gold List after her nomination by Commodos.<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Elles has been the perfect example of an Epic Shadow.  She's always been available to help others no matter what their level.  As a cleric, your responsibilities can become tedious, and can often require you to leave what you are doing to attend to something else.  Elles does this without hesitation whenever possible.  I have never heard anything discouraging from her.  She's always positive, willing to accept a challenge and selfless in helping others.  I recognize that it's not always possible to come to everything that the guild does, but 99% of the time Elles is there ready to assist, even when there isn't a direct benefit for her.  This is our way of saying thanks Elles for everything that you do for us!
<br><br>
 			&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<font color="#FAE42B"><b>Manluin</b></font> - Manluin is one of our newest members of the guild and has been a great asset since day one.  This is Rithmorin's account of the help he received from Manluin, and I agree this is one exemplary Shadow:<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<i>I am in the US ARMY and just prior to the bombing of the WTC in NY my character died in The Overthere.  As a result of the bombing my unit was deployed and I was working long hours and not able to get my corpse back.  Now that things are slowing down I have had time to reunite with the guild and unfortunately try to play a guy with NO armor weapons or coin.  Manluin came to my plea for help when no one else did.  He traveled a great distance to get me armor and even spent a few nights trying for the sole purpose to find me a decent weapon.  After 4 long nights of wandering In High Hold trying to make due with what little coin I could scrounge up, Manluin gave me all that I needed in terms of armor weapons and a new friend that I trust.  He is one thattrulyy needs the gold status.<br></i>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Well done Manluin!  Your dedication and sacrifice is an example for all of us.
<br><br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<font color="#FAE42B"><b>Akronis</b></font> - I got an overwhelming response the night Akronis was nominated for the gold list.  His complete commitment to Epic Shadows was shown in his selfless donation of a Centi Longsword to the guild fun raiser.  This act was only the latest in a long history of hard work and self sacrifice that this Shadow Knight has had with us.  It's my privilege to add Akronis to our gold list.
<br><br>

			</font></p>
